Comprehensive study of the microplastic footprint in the urban pond and river of Eastern India
Mamun Mandal 1, Anamika Roy 1, Abhijit Sarkar 1,
This study quantified and assessed the dynamic footprint of microplastics (MPs) in an urban river and pond in Eastern India. It found MPs in surface water (59–100 particles/litre) and sediment (167–193 particles/gram). Polymer characterization identified nylon (36%) as the dominant type, followed by polyethylene (25%) and polyethylene terephthalate (18%). PubMed Central
The study uses FTIR spectroscopy for polymer identification and evaluates ecological risk — making it methodologically rich and practically relevant.
